items.name: 12-Gauge Casing
items.description: The 12-Gauge Casing is a vital component used in the crafting of 12-Gauge Buckshot Shells and 12-Gauge Slugs .

items.name: 12-Gauge Slug
items.description: 12-Gauge Slugs are used by the Shotguns . Unlike arrows, javelins, and bolts this ammunition is destroyed on impact and cannot be recovered.

items.name: Acidic Glands
items.description: Acidic Glands can be taken to an Organic Residue Cleanser to be turned into 5x Animal Fat . Hazardous when carried in small amounts, deadly when carried in large quantities/with several other Miasmic items. Despite the risk, Acidic Glands is an excellent source of Animal Fat .

items.name: AdLift Module
items.description: This module increases the user's weight capacity by 15% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Ad Lift Modules may be equipped if the prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the amount the user can carry.

items.name: Advanced Aquarium
items.description: The Advanced Aquarium allows Prospectors to store and display their favorite catches. Fish stored in the Advanced Aquarium will not spoil so long as it is connected to a power network providing at least 1,000 units of Power and a water network providing at least 500 units of Water . The Advanced Aquarium will not function if these requirements are not met. The Advanced Aquarium can store 4 fish.

items.name: Advanced Battery Rack
items.description: The Advanced Battery Rack is a power-storing device that must be placed indoors. It can store up to 6,000k Ws of power and can charge/output power at a max rate of 10,000 Watts per second.

items.name: Advanced Creature Deterrent
items.description: While useful for protecting Prospectors from predators, the Advanced Creature Deterrent also prevents the spawning of Fauna so be aware that deer, pronghorns, rabbits, chamois, or other animals will not spawn within the indicated radius.

items.name: Advanced Storm Visor Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Storm Visor Attachment is an end-game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Advanced Armor Attachment Packs in the Tier 4  Tech Tree.

items.name: Advanced Supplemental Filtration Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Supplemental Filtration Attachment is an armor alteration that provides resistance to poison and reduced water consumption.

items.name: Advanced Supplemental Respiration Attachment
items.description: The Advanced Supplemental Respiration Attachment is an end-game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Advanced Armor Attachment Packs in the Tier 4  Tech Tree.

items.name: Advanced Tool Attachment Pack
items.description: The Advanced Tool Attachment Pack is a Tier 4  item that allows Prospectors to alter their tools with additional bonuses. Similar to Tool Attachment Pack , both can be applied at an Alteration Bench or Advanced Alteration Bench .

items.name: Aerodynamic Attachment
items.description: Aerodynamic Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Alpha Wolf Trophy
items.description: Alpha Wolf Trophies are decorative deployables that can be placed on any wall surface and are used to liven any living space. Aside from helping prospectors complete the Bestiary , it can also be used in tandem with other Furniture to increase the Coziness of your living quarters, increasing the duration and effectiveness of the Well Rested Buff .

items.name: Animal Bait
items.description: Animal Bait is used to lure random predators when left in an open area. The blueprint is unlocked account-wide after completing the prospect Wet Work: Extermination . Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Animal Fat
items.description: Animal fat is produced from the rendering down of raw meat and is used in Cooking to make late-game Foods such as Pastry , Fried Chunky Vegetables and, Freshwater Fillet Curry . It is used to create and power the Lantern .

items.name: Animal Healthbar Module
items.description: This module allows the wearer to see creature alert level and health when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot. The Animal Healthbar Module is researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect.

items.name: Animal Highlighting Module
items.description: Animal Highlighting Module is researched and created on the Space Station in the Workshop . Equip in an Envirosuit Module Slot after dropping down for a prospect.

items.description: Anti-Parasitic Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further ailments such as Festering Wounds and Dysentery .

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Tonic
items.description: Used alone to cure parasitic infections such as Festering Wound and Dysentery or as a mid-stage ingredient to the prophylactic Anti-Parasitic Pill

items.name: Anti-Poison Pill
items.description: Anti-Poison Pills are used to cure, and prevent for a short time, further ailments from contact with poisonous substances.

items.name: Anti-Poison Tonic
items.description: Used alone to cure Poison from critters like the Venomous Fish , or as a mid-stage ingredient to the prophylactic Anti-poison Pill .

items.name: Aquarium
items.description: The Aquarium allows Prospectors to store and display their favorite catches. The Aquarium will not function if these requirements are not met. With a full Biofuel Can , the Aquarium will last about three and a half hours. Can only hold 1 fish.

items.name: Archer's Backpack

items.name: Arctic Animal Feed

items.description: The Avocado Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station or the Orbital Exchange Interface and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. items.name: BEAST
items.description: While holding the BEAST, Prospectors can left-click while looking at an animal to "scan" that animal (must be close to the target to initiate a scan). Unlike what the description says, the scanned animal will take additional damage until another scan is performed. Scanning animals using the BEAST also grants 3 bestiary points for the animal scanned.

items.name: Bacon Butty
items.description: Bacon Butty is a consumable food that boosts health, stamina, health regeneration, experience gained and critical damage.

items.name: Banana
items.description: A Banana is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. It can be eaten to boost maximum stamina for 60 seconds and to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Banana Farming Packet
items.description: The Banana Farming Packet is a packet of seeds for planting and growing Bananas . It is unlocked in the Workshop after completing the mission Ape Escape in the Great Hunts Campaigns .

items.name: Barbecue Carrot
items.description: Barbecue Carrot is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Bark Lure
items.description: The Bark Lure can be attached to a Fishing Rod or a Basic Fishing Trap / Advanced Fishing Trap to provide an increase to different attributes detailed in the infobox. The capture zone increase is the size of the capture area during the fishing minigame, increasing the success chance of catching a fish. Like all Lures , the Bark Lure degrades with use and will eventually break after ten uses.

items.name: Basic Battery Rack
items.description: The Basic Battery Rack is a power-storing device that must be placed indoors. It can store up to 1,000k Ws of power and can charge/output power at a max rate of 1,500 Watts per second.

items.name: Basic Fertilizer
items.description: Basic Fertilizer is used on crop plots to enhance the growth of plants. When applied, Crop Yield and Crop Growth Speed is increased by 15% for 1200 seconds. To fertilize a crop plot, equip a fertilizer of your choosing from your hotbar and left click the plot you wish to fertilize.

items.name: Basic Rainwater Purifier
items.description: Basic Rainwater Purifiers can be crafted using Character Crafting with the following resources:

items.name: Basic Riding Saddle
items.description: The Basic Riding Saddle is an item that allows prospectors to ride tamed Mounts . The Basic Riding Saddle can be use on all Mounts (regardless of who tamed them) and comes with two inventory slots and one heavy cargo inventory slot for Equipment . Items stored in the saddle is dropped into a lootable overflow bag when the mount dies.

items.name: Basic Scope Attachment
items.description: Basic Scope Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Ranged Attachment Pack tech. Does not add actual scope to weapon.

items.description: The Battery Cavelight is a portable Light Source that can be deployed on a floor or wall to provide illumination in the surrounding area. It is good for marking a path through caves.

items.name: Battery Spotlight
items.description: The Battery Spotlight is a portable Light Source that can be deployed on a floor or wall to provide illumination in a concentrated area. It is useful as a temporary light source while mining in caves.

items.name: Beehive Extractor

items.name: Biofuel
items.description: Biofuel is a mid-game, Tier 3  fuel that can be crafted or purchased and used to fuel a variety of Deployable equipment and sometimes quest items seen in Missions .

items.name: Biofuel Bio-Cleaner
items.description: The Biofuel Bio-Cleaner is a deployable Tier 3  cleaning device that can process organic materials collected from world bosses into Legendary Biomass and clean infected materials found on Prometheus , similar to the Tier 4  Organic Residue Cleanser .

items.name: Biofuel Can
items.description: Biofuel Can is used to store Biofuel . It is filled at either the Biofuel Composter or Electric Composter .

items.name: Biofuel Chimney Cap
items.description: A Biofuel Chimney Cap is the final cap piece to place on a Biofuel Chimney Extension or directly on a Biofuel Fireplace . Two variants, a half height and full height, are available by holding the 'R' key when deploying.

items.name: Biofuel Chimney Extension
items.description: A Biofuel Chimney Extension is a wide round section of metal chimney or stove pipe to place on a Biofuel Fireplace or another existing Biofuel Chimney Extension to extend the chimney vertically. It is usually capped with a Biofuel Chimney Cap .

items.name: Biofuel Composter
items.description: The Biofuel Composter enables the Prospector to produce Biofuel . Can be connected to a water network providing at least 100 units of water to increase processing speed, but is not required to produce Biofuel.

items.name: Biofuel Fireplace
items.description: The Biofuel Fireplace is deployable Tier 3  version of the Fireplace that burns Biofuel to provide a source of heat, a source of light , Coziness and a means to cook Food indoors.

items.name: Biofuel Generator
items.description: The Biofuel Generator generates Electricity when supplied with biofuel from a Biofuel Can . Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power.

items.name: Biofuel Lamp
items.description: Provides exceptional lightning compared to the Torch or Lantern . Can be equipped in the "L" light slot on the hotbar.

items.name: Biofuel Oxite Dissolver
items.description: More efficient than the Oxite Dissolver , this is used in tandem with Oxygen Containers placed into the oxidizer. The front slots of the deployable only accept Oxygen Containers and will automatically fill said containers from Oxite placed into the machine when supplied with Biofuel from a Biofuel Can . A full Biofuel Can will last three minutes and twenty seconds, producing 0.2 Liters of Oxygen every two seconds.

items.name: Biofuel Stove
items.description: The Biofuel Stove is a mid- to late-game technology that expands the recipes available compared to the Potbelly Stove . It requires Biofuel to run and must be snapped to a side of the Kitchen Bench .

items.name: Biofuel Water Pump
items.description: The Biofuel Water Pump outputs 1,000 Water when supplied with biofuel; use the Water Pipe Tool to connect it to Crafting Benches / Water Storage to provide water. The Biofuel Water Pump can output water for two hours and thirty minutes with a full Biofuel Can .

items.name: Biotech Maul

items.name: Campfire
items.description: The first available cooking station, the campfire is an essential early structure that allows prospectors to pass the night and to cook Raw Meat or Fish Chunks , yielding safe to consume versions.

items.name: Canteen
items.description: Filled at any water source, including a Rain Reservoir . The Canteen is water tight, and is a mid-game item requiring a Machining Bench . Canteens can hold 5.0 L of water, 5 times as much as a water skin and can keep the Prospector hydrated for approximately 10x as long due to the leakage of the water skin.

items.name: Carbon Javelin
items.description: The Carbon Javelin is a variant of the Carbon Spear that can only be thrown and is a cheaper upgrade to the Platinum Javelin that deals more damage and has a lower break chance.

Crafted in batches of five and stacks up to twenty.

items.description: A Electric Chimney Cap is the final cap piece to place on an Electric Chimney Extension or directly on an Electric Fireplace .

items.description: A Electric Chimney Extension is a wide flat section of metal chimney or stove pipe to place on a Electric Fireplace or another existing Electric Chimney Extension to extend the chimney vertically. It is usually capped with a Electric Chimney Cap .

items.name: Electric Composter
items.description: The Electric Composter enables the Prospector to produce Biofuel at an accelerated rate compared to the Biofuel Composter . An active power connection providing at least 1500 units is required to operate the Electric Composter. Similar to the Biofuel Composter , an active Water source increases processing speed and is not required.

items.name: Electric Dehumidifier
items.description: The Electric Dehumidifier allows for cave exploration without the risk of catching Cave Sickness while also preventing cave worms from spawning within its effective range. Will not prevent creatures from spawning when activating Thumpers , Radars, or other mission items that have been placed or activated.

items.name: Electric Extractor
items.description: The Electric Extractor is used to extract Exotics from Exotic Deposits. A connection providing at least 1,500 units of power is required.

items.name: Electric Fireplace
items.description: The Electric Fireplace is Tier 4  version of the Fireplace that is powered by Electricity to provide a source of heat, a source of light , Coziness and a means to cook Food indoors. At least 250 units of electricity are required to power the fireplace.

items.name: Electric Stove
items.description: The Electric Stove is a late-game technology that provides a more robust cooking experience and expands the recipes available compared to the Biofuel Stove . It requires 1,000 units of Power to function and must be snapped to a side of a Marble Kitchen Bench or Kitchen Bench .

items.name: Electric Water Pump
items.description: The Electric Water Pump provides Water when supplied with electricity, use the Water Pipe Tool to connect it to Crafting Benches / Water Storage to provide water. Requires 1,000 units of Electricity to function and outputs 1,000 units of Water .

items.name: Electricity Tool
items.description: The Electricity Tool connects Power Sources to Deployables / Power Storage to provide Electricity .

items.name: Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer
items.description: The Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer produces oxygen from water, removing the need for Oxite . Requires 1,550 Watts and 500 Liters per second to function. The Electrolytic Oxygen Synthesizer can hold up to 10 Oxygen Containers and will auto fill tanks in seconds.

Must be connected to Electricity and Water providing at least 1,000 Watts and 30 liters per second to function.

items.name: Fire Extinguisher
items.description: The Fire Extinguisher is a Tier 3  tool used to hastily put out fires. As Prospectors use the Fire Extinguisher, its durability decreases and cannot be repaired at the Machining Bench when broken.

items.name: Fire Whacker
items.description: The Fire Whacker is used to put out brush fires on the ground, other players who are on fire, or structures that are ablaze from lightning strikes. The Fire Whacker can also be used to put yourself out - aim down at your feet and start whacking; cannot be in/on source of fire while attempting to use the fire whacker on yourself.

items.name: Firepit
items.description: The Firepit is an upgrade to the Campfire , providing significantly more heat, increased inventory size, and is marginally faster at processing. Due to the increased weight of the Firepit, it should only be deployed in structures that provide adequate support.

items.name: Fireplace
items.description: The Fireplace is deployable stone and wood building piece that provides a source of heat, a source of light, Coziness and a safer alternative to cooking Food than the Campfire . It provides an indoor source of heat that allows the prospector to avoid inadvertently setting themselves ablaze.

items.name: Flamethrower

items.description: Soy Bean Stir-Fry is a Food with a unique Status Effect , which can be stacked with other food buffs. Can be eaten to satisfy Hunger .

items.name: Splint

items.name: Spoiled Plants
items.description: Spoiled Plants are the byproduct of spoiled food like vegetables and fruit, and are used to craft Volatile Substance or Basic Fertilizer for Crop Plots. Cannot be eaten despite having the You Gonna Eat That? talent.

items.name: Squash Farming Packet
items.description: The Squash Farming Packet is unlocked in the Workshop on the Space Station and is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. Only after landing on Icarus can the packet be consumed, giving the Prospector five Squash seeds, which then can be planted in Dirt Mounds or crop plots to grow Plant Resources .

items.name: Stabilized Exotics
items.description: Stabilized Exotics are a form of currency in the Workshop and the stabilized state that results from processing and cleaning Volatile Raw Exotics found on Prometheus .

items.name: Stamina
items.description: Stamina is a power gauge that fuels many of the actions in Icarus. Using tools, sprinting, jumping, attacking, and crafting all require stamina. Status Effects can increase or decrease max stamina or stamina regeneration. A prospector who runs out of stamina becomes exhausted and cannot perform stamina-consuming actions until they've regained a significant portion of their stamina.

items.name: Stealth
items.description: Stealth is concealment from Fauna found on Icarus, and determines how both hostile and passive creatures react to your presence. Hunting is an important task for most Icarus prospectors. It provides a renewable source of Food Items , but also a number of Resources essential to survival.

items.name: Storm Visor Attachment
items.description: Storm Visor Attachment is a mid-to-end game item available once the prospector has unlocked the Armor Attachment Pack tech.

items.name: Strength Boost Module
items.description: When equipped in a module slot of an Envirosuit , this module increases the carry weight capacity of Prospectors near the user, however it does not affect the wearers max carry weight. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop .

items.name: Strengthened Strings Attachment

items.name: Super Cooled Ice
items.description: Super Cooled Ice is a resource required to make Cold Steel Ingots , a precursor resource used in making Cold Steel Tools , Weapons , and Ammo .

items.name: Survival Animal Feed
items.description: Survival Animal Feed is an Animal Feed for Pets or Mounts with a unique Status Effect . Can be fed to mounts to satisfy Hunger . Survival Animal Feed decays in 10,800 seconds, but that decay can be slowed down by storing Survival Animal Feed inside an Ice Box or Refrigerator .

items.name: Survival Backpack
items.description: The Survival Backpack is a must need when taking long trips across Icarus, fit everything you need inside for survival! Innovative storage system that mitigates injuries.

items.name: Survival Kit
items.description: Survival Kits are a Tier 3  bandage that heals basic wounds, deep wounds, frostbite and heatstroke Status Effects . It replaces a number of basic items, but requires considerably more materials to craft.

items.name: Survival Module
items.description: This module increases the user's resistance to cold/hot environments, reducing the damage taken from Hypothermia/Hyperthermia. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Survival Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the users resistance to hyperthermia/hypothermia.

items.name: Suture Kit
items.description: A Suture Kit is used to treat a Deep Wound, Hemorrhage or Exotic Deep Wound.

items.name: Synthetic Enzymes
items.description: Synthetic Enzymes are a crafted variant of Condensed Enzymes that can be used as fuel in a Localized Terraforming Device . Unlike Condensed Enzymes , the synthetic version is less potent as a fuel but does not require constructing, placing or defending a Vapor Condenser on an Enzyme Geyser .

items.name: Tackle Box
items.description: The Tackle Box is a storage deployable that can be used to store a handful of lures and caught fish. Unlike other storage deployables, the Tackle Box can be picked up with items inside and does not require shelter to be used. With 3 slots for Lures and 2 slots that will halt the spoil timer of any caught fish, the Tackle Box is a handy tool for fishing adventures.

items.name: Target Dummy
items.description: Target Dummys are deployable items used to test out weapons and to see their damage output when hitting hard points and weak points.

items.name: Water
items.description: Water is a basic resource needed for survival on Icarus. It may be consumed by drinking from natural water sources such as lakes, streams, and pools found in Caves . Water from these natural sources is Tainted Water and has a 15% chance of causing dysentery. Water has various levels of purity depending on source and means of filtering. A status icon is displayed to indicate the type and status of water the prospector has consumed.

items.name: Water Barrel
items.description: Water Barrels are a deployable that can be connected to a water network to store 300,000 water and can output 1,000 water per second to keep the network operational.

items.name: Water Bomb
items.description: The Water Bomb is a Tier 2  item that will aid Prospectors in extinguishing fires. Once thrown, the Water Bomb will douse the area in water, putting out any fires. Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Water Pipe Tool
items.description: The Water Pipe Tool connects the Biofuel Water Pump / Electric Water Pump to Deployables / Water Storage to provide Water .

items.name: Water Purifier
items.description: Water Purifiers can be crafted from the Machining Bench with the following resources once the appropriate blueprint point has been spent:

items.name: Water Sprinkler
items.description: The Water Sprinkler will provide fire suppression when connected to a Water Network with a Water Pipe Tool . Can be manually activated by damaging it or by pressing F to water nearby Dirt Mounds / Crop Plots or to apply the Wet modifier to nearby prospectors and deployables, which can help counter heatwaves in Deserts .

items.name: Water Treatment Pill
items.description: Water Treatment Pills remove the risk of dysentery from Tainted and Rainwater. Use with any canteen of water using the Character Crafting interface

items.name: Water Trough
items.description: The Water Trough is a basic trough used to keep Mounts and Pets hydrated. Can be filled using a Liquid Container filled with Water or by leaving it exposed to the elements.

items.name: Water Wheel
items.description: The Water Wheel is a power-generating device that can be placed in any flowing body of water. Use an Electricity Tool to connect it to Benches to provide power.

items.name: Watering Can
items.description: The Watering Can is a mid-game Tool used to water multiple crop plots/dirt mounds simultaneously. Prospectors can unlock it in Tier 2  portion of the Tech Tree after reaching Level 20. The Watering Can hold 5.0 L and can be used five times before needing to be refilled.
